RuiWang-CNN:
1. nn.convlayers.conv_forward:
    a) same parameter name C in z and K will cause some confusions
2. nn.convlayers.conv_backward:
    a) float64 is too huge, should use float32 for faster GPU calculations
3. Should make CNN classes more flexible, e.g.:
    myCNN = CNN(**kwargs)
    myCNN.convolution(**kwargs)
    myCNN.relu(**kwargs)
    myCNN.maxpooling(**kwargs)
    myCNN.relu(**kwargs)
    myCNN.forward(**kwargs)
    myCNN.flatten(**kwargs)
    myCNN.backpropagation()

4. Do not see the dropout in the CNN yet.
5. Use pytorch instead of Numpy for making use of GPU speed




